	   <tr><td colspan=2>Because Verant uses it as a mark of honour. That character was at that particular place, to get that particular item. Trust me when I say there is nothing more disheartening to see a L2 bard in full class armour (the glowing blue suit) and me at L34 with banded armour (just about to go off and get my quest armour). <br>Did that character do the quests? No.... Should a L2 bard be wearing that armour... doubtful (T'was handed down in my family through the ages... sure it was)... Was the armour earned by the _person_ who now plays that character? yes, of course it was. <br><br>But (and here I agree with Verant) one reason for the no-drop items was to stop this item passing. Lore didn't do it. So now we have Lore, No-drop, and "common" items.<br><br>Durus Stoneguard<br>Initiate of the 34th Mystery of Brell Serilis<br>Povar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
